---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../lib/config';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Rustam Salavatov — solo founder, AI engineer. Building products with AI agents.">
  <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none" data-pagefind-body>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-5 not-prose mb-6">
      <img src={SITE.author.avatar} alt={SITE.author.name} class="w-20 h-20 rounded-full" width="80" height="80" />
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold">{SITE.author.name}</h1>
        <p class="text-[var(--color-muted)]">{SITE.author.shortBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>Hi, I'm Rustam.</p>

    <p>I'm a solo founder and AI engineer. I build products with AI agents — tools designed for people who value simplicity, privacy, and speed.</p>

    <h2>What I'm Building</h2>

    <p><a href="/projects/project-superduperai">SuperDuperAI</a> is a product studio, not a single product.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Video Editor</strong> — AI-powered video creation platform. Turn vibes into videos instantly. Multi-agent AI system for professional video creation without skills, equipment, or budget.</li>
      <li><strong>Super Chatbot</strong> — Multi-agent chatbot platform with <a href="/wiki/rag-patterns">RAG</a>, tool use, and custom knowledge bases. Deploy on web, Telegram, or WhatsApp.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/projects/project-facealarm">FaceAlarm</a></strong> — Face yoga tracker with daily selfie alarm. AI-powered alarm won't turn off until you take a selfie.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/projects/project-kubizbeat">Jaw Harp Synth</a></strong> — Digital kubyz (jaw harp) synthesizer for iOS. Traditional instrument sounds with modern digital effects.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Each one started as a simple hypothesis, was <a href="/wiki/startup-validation">validated fast</a>, and follows the same principles: AI-first, privacy-respecting, minimal, useful. Everything I build is open source or shared on <a href={SITE.social.github}>GitHub</a>.</p>

    <h2>Manifesto</h2>

    <p><em>Not where everyone is — where I'm the only one.</em></p>

    <p>I started <a href="/projects/project-life2film">Life2Film</a> in 2014 — tools to turn everyday moments into stories. The technology wasn't ready. I closed it in 2021. The dream never left. SuperDuperAI is the second chapter of the same story.</p>

    <p>Building products is how I think. Each one is an experiment — a question asked to the world. Creativity is freedom. AI and agents don't replace human creativity — they remove the friction so I can focus on what matters: ideas, craft, time with people I love.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>AI is the foundation, not a feature.</strong> <a href="/wiki/schema-guided-reasoning">Schemas first</a>, then logic.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/wiki/privacy-as-architecture">Privacy is architecture</a></strong>, not a feature. On-device, local storage, no accounts when possible.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/wiki/one-pain-one-feature-launch">One pain → one feature → launch.</a></strong> If nobody wants it — <a href="/wiki/kill-iterate-scale">kill it</a> and move on.</li>
      <li><strong><a href="/wiki/antifragile-life-design">Antifragile</a></strong> — modular, <a href="/wiki/portfolio-approach">small bets</a>, asymmetric upside.</li>
      <li><strong>Open source by default.</strong> Knowledge compounds when it's shared.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>I should be a creator, not a robot. Technology should free humans to create, to reflect, to live.</p>

    <p><a href="/posts/manifest" class="font-mono">Read full manifesto &rarr;</a></p>

